  "text": "In the second stage, covariates with a strong indication of impact in univariate models on the rate parameters (y 0 , c, e, and p) were included in the construction of additive multivariate models. All combinations containing at least one of the covariates were evaluated. Covariates with a Pearson correlation coefficient .0.60 were not added simultaneously as covariates to the same rate parameter. We used AIC, DAIC, and AIC weights when selecting the best model for inference of covariate impact [CITATION_1] .",
